name Spicy Pickled Eggs
serves 8 pieces 2
note <p>The eggs keep for one week.</p>
  <p>To serve: halve the egg and lift out the yolk. Add a little salt, pepper, vinegar,
  oil and mustard to each egg white half, then replace the yolk.</p>
tags preserve, starter, snacks, vegetarian

# Preparation

- 8 eggs
Hard boil, refresh in cold water and peel.
-> eggs

- 2 onions
@nodep
Halve unpeeled and toast cut-side down in a dry pan until golden brown.
-> onions

- 60 g sugar
- 60 g salt
- 1 tbsp mustard seeds
- 1 tbsp caraway seeds
- 1 tbsp black peppercorns
- 1 "red chilli"
- 3 juniper berries
- 2 allspice berries
- 1 bay leaf
- 200 ml white wine vinegar
= onions
Bring {1.3} litres of water with the onions, sugar, salt, spices and vinegar to a boil.
Once the sugar and salt have dissolved, simmer gently over low heat for 5 minutes. Remove
from the heat and leave to cool.
-> brine

- 1 bunch dill
- 1 bunch flat-leaf parsley
- 0.5 bunch tarragon
- 1 strip lemon zest
@nodep
Wash the herbs.
-> herbs

= eggs
= brine
= herbs
Layer the lemon zest, herbs and eggs in a sufficiently large, well-sealing jar. Pour over
the cooled brine and leave to infuse for about 24 hours.
